article.headline: Oklahoma St. 82, Texas A&amp,M-Corpus Christi 59
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas -- Obi Muonelo's 32 points and 14 rebounds helped Oklahoma State defeat Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 82-59 on Sunday. Muonelo hit eight 3-pointers and had 12 defensive rebounds. James Anderson added 16 points for the Cowboys (6-3). Terrel Harris scored 11 and Malcoln Kirkland had 10. Kevin Palmer led the Islanders (5-5) with 14 points. LaMarr Drake added 12. Texas A&M-Corpus Christi led 31-29 at the half. After shooting only 39 percent from the field in the first half, the Cowboys shot 77 percent in the second half.
